Dia. 01 Correct Answer
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's \cf1\b placement \cf0\b0 at 1 is a \cf1\b severe\cf0\b0  vital point.
\par
\par As it was already said several times, the 1-2 point is a great place.
\par
\par Black 2 is the strongest answer then White plays dansu at 3 and it becomes pae.
\par
\par This is the \cf1\b best \cf0\b0 result for \cf1\b both players\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par }
